FBIS4-58943 "drnes090_c_94008" FBIS-NES-94-090 Daily Report 2 May 1994 Egypt `Terrorist' Financier Operating From Netherlands `Terrorist' Financier Operating From Netherlands NC0905153494 Cairo AL-WAFD in Arabic 2 May 94 p 12 NC0905153494 Cairo AL-WAFD Arabic BFN [Report by Mustafa al-Buhayri in London; from the "Good Day" column] [Text] Millionaire Usamah Bin-Ladin, the primary source of financing for terrorist groups in Egypt and the Arab world, has requested political asylum in Holland. Bin-Ladin, whose Saudi nationality has been withdrawn, manages his terrorist activities from Holland. He left Sudan after bombs were thrown at his home recently. Bin-Ladin currently distributes leaflets opposed to Arab governments and regimes.
